Defendant Stephan G Lawrenz in court with attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris.  James E. Fitzgerald appeared for the State of Wisconsin along with Assistant District Attorney Jayne Dewire.  State makes sentencing recommendations.  Defense makes sentencing recommendations.  Michele Behrens makes statements.  Mr. Barber makes statements.  Defendant makes statements.  The defendant was sentenced to the following:
Count 1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

48 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 490 days)
  -  24 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  24 MONTHS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling; 
*Perform 60-Hours Community Service. 

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (Apply Cash Bail) (to be paid as a condition of probation);
DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (Apply Cash Bail) (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

CONDITION TIME: 90 days HUBER, the last 30-days are STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  
Defendant is to report on 12-1-17 at 4:00 p.m.
Sentence may be served in Dane County.

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
